main event: A civilian witness observed a stationary object in the western sky over Brentwood, Long Island, New York on October 29, 1966. The object emitted a bright blue-white light and then sped off at a very fast rate of speed.
interesting points: The witness took photographs of the object, but when the film was developed, there was an additional unidentified object in the photos that the witness did not see during the sighting.
The object was described as stationary at first, then it suddenly sped off at an extremely fast rate of speed.
The object appeared to be oval or disc-shaped and changed colors from bluish-green to bluish-white.
Other witnesses in the area reported seeing similar objects with different color variations.
The object's speed and flight path were inconsistent with a conventional aircraft.
